ozwell.s1: The two notes are very similar. Both describe the case of an 18-year-old male with a right shoulder injury following an assault. They detail the patient's history, physical examination findings, radiographic findings, and the proposed treatment plan, which includes open reduction and reconstruction of the proximal humerus. Both notes mention the patient's inability to move the shoulder without discomfort, the fracture and dislocation of the proximal humerus, and the surgical approach to address the issue. Additionally, they both outline the post-procedure follow-up with physical therapy.
